flowRoot.flowPara: My Android app sends the sensor data as a CSV file, via email.
Splits data into segments, then averages data within each segment.
helps reduce low frequency effects, e.g, gravity
Data is sliced from the CSV file and stored in data structures, VectorSet and QuaternionSet.
These custom data structures inherit from NumPy's "ndarray". This allows them to be seamlessly used with algorithms from packages including NumPy, SciPy, etc.

flowPara.flowSpan: Measures the acceleration force in m/s
that is applied to a device on all three physical axes (x, y, and z),

flowRoot.flowPara: Measures the orientation of a device by providing in quaternion form (x, y, z, and w).
Data will be sent real-time with Bluetooth.
OpenGL can then be used for visualizing real-time position of the phone.
Orientation must be applied to the local acceleration (along the phone's axes) to obtain global acceleration (along the world's axes)
Position is calculated by integrating acceleration twice.
Cumulative trapezoids is the method of integration being used.
